1
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:03,240
Uncle Rut.

2
00:03:04,600 --> 00:03:05,760
Uncle Rut, what happened?

3
00:03:05,840 --> 00:03:08,720
Your aunt, of course.
She's been keeping snakes.

4
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:10,400
Aunt Nong? Keeping snakes?

5
00:03:10,480 --> 00:03:14,320
I was just about to open the door,
but there were snakes everywhere.

6
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:16,480
No way. I'm calling Aunt Nong.

7
00:03:16,560 --> 00:03:19,240
Wait, wait, Sin. Can you not rush?

8
00:03:19,320 --> 00:03:21,440
How can I not rush? This is serious.

9
00:03:21,520 --> 00:03:23,200
Can't we find out the truth first?

10
00:03:23,280 --> 00:03:25,600
I can just call and ask.
How else should I find out?

11
00:03:25,680 --> 00:03:28,080
You know what your aunt's like.

12
00:03:28,160 --> 00:03:29,680
- Your aunt is--
- Excuse me.

13
00:03:30,280 --> 00:03:32,000
I think
we shouldn't blame anyone just yet.

14
00:03:32,080 --> 00:03:34,400
It's cold these days,
so these guys tend to slither…

15
00:03:35,440 --> 00:03:36,760
I mean the snakes.

16
00:03:37,360 --> 00:03:39,360
I already checked around,

17
00:03:39,440 --> 00:03:43,760
and I found a rotten gap. They could've
gotten in through it to look for warmth.

18
00:03:43,840 --> 00:03:46,800
Is it possible they were pet snakes?

19
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:49,320
Well, they probably weren't pets.

20
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:52,200
First of all,
there's no snake food around here.

21
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:54,280
- I checked everywhere.
- Mm.

22
00:03:54,360 --> 00:03:55,760
And secondly.

23
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:57,800
This kind of snake
isn't commonly kept as a pet.

24
00:03:58,400 --> 00:03:59,440
They've all been caught?

25
00:03:59,520 --> 00:04:00,760
Yes.

26
00:04:00,840 --> 00:04:03,720
- Well, that's a relief.
- Alright.

27
00:04:03,800 --> 00:04:05,280
- Thank you so much.
- You're welcome. I'll get going.

28
00:04:05,360 --> 00:04:06,200
- Alright.
- Goodbye.

29
00:04:21,320 --> 00:04:24,600
Very impressive, Mr. Det.
Next time, I'll increase the weight a bit.

30
00:04:26,640 --> 00:04:28,400
Isn't Ameena coming today?

31
00:04:28,960 --> 00:04:29,960
Well, Ms. Ameena…

32
00:04:31,160 --> 00:04:32,640
I haven't seen her today.

33
00:04:33,560 --> 00:04:35,160
Did she call to postpone?

34
00:04:39,360 --> 00:04:40,600
No, not at all.

35
00:04:41,360 --> 00:04:42,680
Is something wrong?

36
00:04:44,160 --> 00:04:45,560
She's probably fine.

37
00:04:45,640 --> 00:04:48,520
- She'll probably come.
- Then I'll call her.

38
00:04:48,600 --> 00:04:49,720
No need.

39
00:04:50,440 --> 00:04:53,240
Just leave her be.
She'll probably call herself.

40
00:04:53,960 --> 00:04:55,880
Then I won't call her.

41
00:05:18,240 --> 00:05:21,040
If you're worried,
you should call her, Mr. Det.

42
00:05:23,520 --> 00:05:27,600
That's true. I guess I'll try calling.
So you won't have to wait long.

43
00:05:34,160 --> 00:05:38,000
Hello, Na. Are you coming
to the gym today? The trainer is waiting.

44
00:05:38,080 --> 00:05:39,520
No.

45
00:05:39,600 --> 00:05:42,040
If you're not coming, why didn't you call?
You left him sitting here waiting.

46
00:05:42,120 --> 00:05:44,440
Then let him deduct the time.

47
00:05:44,520 --> 00:05:46,520
My business is more important.

48
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:49,720
What business? Don't you even
have to tell me anymore?

49
00:05:49,800 --> 00:05:51,200
Serious business.

50
00:05:51,280 --> 00:05:53,960
<i>You're an architect, Det.</i>
<i>You wouldn't understand.</i>

51
00:05:54,040 --> 00:05:56,920
You wouldn't be able to help
or decide anything anyway.

52
00:05:57,640 --> 00:06:00,400
Just do your own work. That's enough.

53
00:06:00,480 --> 00:06:01,720
Where are you?

54
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:06,440
With someone
who actually understands business.

55
00:06:06,520 --> 00:06:08,000
- Was there anything else?
- Wait.

56
00:06:08,720 --> 00:06:10,960
Who is that person
who understands business?

57
00:06:13,160 --> 00:06:14,320
My father.

58
00:06:15,920 --> 00:06:17,160
I gotta go.

59
00:06:22,400 --> 00:06:23,360
Let's go.

60
00:06:33,160 --> 00:06:34,560
So is Ms. Ameena coming or not?

61
00:06:38,880 --> 00:06:42,000
It's okay, Mr. Det.
There's only one set left. The last set.

62
00:06:43,160 --> 00:06:44,080
Enough.

63
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:46,400
There's only one set left, Mr. Det.

64
00:06:57,160 --> 00:06:59,360
I think this project is good.

65
00:06:59,440 --> 00:07:02,560
It really enhances
the image of Vanich Mall.

66
00:07:03,160 --> 00:07:05,320
So, girls, how far have you gotten?

67
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:08,720
Som, we still have four projects left
and we haven't decided

68
00:07:08,800 --> 00:07:10,880
which one to present to Vanich Mall.

69
00:07:10,960 --> 00:07:12,320
- Let me see.
- Alright.

70
00:07:12,400 --> 00:07:14,240
ONE DEVICE PER CHILD PROJECT
"YOU SHARE, SO THEY CAN STUDY"

71
00:07:14,320 --> 00:07:15,880
Mm, interesting.

72
00:07:15,960 --> 00:07:18,160
That one's my project, Som.

73
00:07:19,280 --> 00:07:20,760
You've improved a lot.

74
00:07:22,840 --> 00:07:26,400
Now I get why you can't choose.
They're all interesting.

75
00:07:26,920 --> 00:07:29,040
Som, someone's here to see you.

76
00:07:51,160 --> 00:07:52,720
Hello, Mrs. Wanee.

77
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:54,600
You came so suddenly,

78
00:07:54,680 --> 00:07:57,840
I didn't prepare a room. I'll have
someone prepare the reception room.

79
00:07:57,920 --> 00:08:00,760
No need for formalities.

80
00:08:00,840 --> 00:08:05,560
I just wanted to come and see
how the children here really live.

81
00:08:06,960 --> 00:08:08,560
Yes, Mrs. Wanee.

82
00:08:13,640 --> 00:08:16,080
The children look happy.

83
00:08:16,160 --> 00:08:19,800
Yes. Their happiness
is the most important thing to us.

84
00:08:19,880 --> 00:08:21,280
I'm curious.

85
00:08:21,360 --> 00:08:24,160
Why did you suddenly change your mind?

86
00:08:24,240 --> 00:08:25,520
I'm sorry?

87
00:08:26,520 --> 00:08:30,040
Baan Saeng Wan Mai
already proposed a project once before.

88
00:08:30,120 --> 00:08:32,559
At the time, I was interested.

89
00:08:32,640 --> 00:08:36,000
I wanted to support
the children's education.

90
00:08:36,080 --> 00:08:37,679
And then suddenly,

91
00:08:37,760 --> 00:08:40,120
you guys were the ones who canceled it.

92
00:08:41,280 --> 00:08:43,000
I sincerely apologize.

93
00:08:43,080 --> 00:08:45,600
At the time,
we weren't ready in many ways.

94
00:08:45,680 --> 00:08:48,840
We were worried that if we proposed it,
there would be paperwork issues.

95
00:08:50,040 --> 00:08:52,520
So now you're going to do it again?

96
00:08:53,120 --> 00:08:56,800
Yes. We believe that
if we receive this funding,

97
00:08:56,880 --> 00:08:59,200
it will improve
the children's quality of life

98
00:08:59,280 --> 00:09:01,680
and give them a better education.

99
00:09:03,920 --> 00:09:06,680
Lack of document readiness is one thing.

100
00:09:07,240 --> 00:09:09,400
Transparency is another.

101
00:09:10,040 --> 00:09:14,040
And financial necessity
is yet another matter.

102
00:09:14,120 --> 00:09:16,160
Yes, Mrs. Wanee.

103
00:09:17,840 --> 00:09:19,920
Som, do you know

104
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:22,520
that before I reached this point,

105
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:26,080
I had my share of hardships too?

106
00:09:27,040 --> 00:09:28,240
Most importantly,

107
00:09:28,320 --> 00:09:31,920
everything can always be discussed.

108
00:09:32,840 --> 00:09:34,320
Yes, Mrs. Wanee.

109
00:09:34,400 --> 00:09:39,240
So don't let incomplete paperwork
destroy the children's future.

110
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:42,760
I'm more than willing to help.

111
00:09:42,840 --> 00:09:46,920
So the paperwork
can be sent later. I understand.

112
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:48,760
Thank you very much.

113
00:09:52,120 --> 00:09:54,160
I mean, I'm not the one in the wrong.

114
00:09:54,800 --> 00:09:57,320
But if I buy something for her,
will Ameena…

115
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:04,120
These products should be suitable for
the project we were discussing, Ameena.

116
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:06,240
Hey, I gotta go now.

117
00:10:06,320 --> 00:10:08,320
This section is all clothing.

118
00:10:11,120 --> 00:10:12,560
Didn't you say you were with your dad?

119
00:10:14,920 --> 00:10:16,040
I was.

120
00:10:18,120 --> 00:10:19,360
Ameena.

121
00:10:20,480 --> 00:10:22,560
Are you going to settle this nonsense,

122
00:10:23,240 --> 00:10:24,920
or are you going to
talk business with me first?

123
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:25,920
What nonsense?

124
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:27,680
Come on, we're adults.

125
00:10:27,760 --> 00:10:29,240
Don't act jealous.

126
00:10:29,320 --> 00:10:30,720
It's unprofessional, you know?

127
00:10:30,800 --> 00:10:32,440
What kind of person are you?

128
00:10:32,520 --> 00:10:35,080
Det, show some respect to our partner.

129
00:10:35,160 --> 00:10:38,440
Respect? Does someone like him
deserve any respect?

130
00:10:38,520 --> 00:10:39,760
Watch your mouth.

131
00:10:40,520 --> 00:10:41,920
I haven't even done anything to her.

132
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:43,760
You say you love Kluay,

133
00:10:43,840 --> 00:10:46,960
but then you're here with another woman.
How exactly am I supposed to see you?

134
00:10:47,040 --> 00:10:49,840
How you see me?
What does that have to do with me?

135
00:10:50,960 --> 00:10:53,120
Det, I think you misunderstood.

136
00:10:53,200 --> 00:10:56,280
Warat and I
really do have business to discuss.

137
00:10:58,680 --> 00:11:00,080
Go home.

138
00:11:01,120 --> 00:11:01,960
We'll talk at home.

139
00:11:11,120 --> 00:11:12,800
Thank you, Mrs. Wanee.

140
00:11:12,880 --> 00:11:15,760
Alright. Take good care of the children.

141
00:11:15,840 --> 00:11:17,640
If you need anything, tell Supol.

142
00:11:19,800 --> 00:11:21,760
Oh, one more thing.

143
00:11:23,080 --> 00:11:24,360
Toi isn't here?

144
00:11:24,960 --> 00:11:27,600
She had an urgent meeting in Korat.

145
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:31,080
That's a shame. I was hoping to see her.

146
00:11:31,160 --> 00:11:33,400
- So we could talk about…
- Talk about what?

147
00:11:33,480 --> 00:11:35,080
You can tell me and I'll pass it on.

148
00:11:35,160 --> 00:11:37,480
About your sister
being engaged to my grandson.

149
00:11:38,800 --> 00:11:41,000
Oh, about that, Mom probably still…

150
00:11:41,080 --> 00:11:44,240
Don't tell me your mom still doesn't know.

151
00:11:44,920 --> 00:11:47,680
No, she doesn't know yet.

152
00:11:47,760 --> 00:11:51,680
What is this? Something this big?
How could she not know?

153
00:11:53,440 --> 00:11:54,640
- Well, Kluay…
- Then,

154
00:11:54,720 --> 00:11:57,280
what's the point
of them already being engaged?

155
00:11:59,400 --> 00:12:01,440
With the utmost respect, ma'am,

156
00:12:01,520 --> 00:12:03,440
they probably wanted
to talk among themselves first.

157
00:12:03,520 --> 00:12:04,920
That won't do.

158
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:08,280
Something like this has to be acknowledged
by the elders on both sides.

159
00:12:08,360 --> 00:12:09,680
This isn't child's play.

160
00:12:10,600 --> 00:12:11,920
- Well…
- Ma'am,

161
00:12:12,560 --> 00:12:14,680
kids these days
aren't like our generation.

162
00:12:14,760 --> 00:12:17,800
In our generation, if our parents told us
to do something, we did it immediately.

163
00:12:17,880 --> 00:12:19,680
- And kids these days…
- What?

164
00:12:19,760 --> 00:12:21,040
What about kids these days?

165
00:12:21,120 --> 00:12:23,520
Oh, so you mean
they don't have to listen to us anymore?

166
00:12:24,840 --> 00:12:28,000
With the utmost respect,
just one more time, ma'am,

167
00:12:28,080 --> 00:12:31,440
I think they probably want to talk first,
settle things between themselves first.

168
00:12:31,520 --> 00:12:32,840
They probably don't want
to involve elders like us yet.

169
00:12:32,920 --> 00:12:35,040
But they are serious.

170
00:12:35,120 --> 00:12:36,880
He even gave her his mom's ring.

171
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:41,200
Ma'am, they believe
their lives belong to them.

172
00:12:41,280 --> 00:12:43,000
They want to live their own lives.

173
00:12:43,080 --> 00:12:45,560
They want to choose their own partners.

174
00:12:45,640 --> 00:12:47,680
And once they've decided,

175
00:12:47,760 --> 00:12:49,800
that's when they'll come tell us adults.

176
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:53,440
- Yes, well, these days, it's…
- Fine, fine.

177
00:12:53,520 --> 00:12:54,440
I understand now.

178
00:12:55,560 --> 00:12:59,280
Today, I actually intended
to come speak with your mom

179
00:12:59,360 --> 00:13:01,440
so that the elders on both sides

180
00:13:01,520 --> 00:13:04,600
could discuss this properly.

181
00:13:04,680 --> 00:13:08,400
Yes. If Mom comes back soon,
I will let her know right away.

182
00:13:08,480 --> 00:13:10,920
No need to make such a big deal out of it.

183
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:15,480
Because now I understand that
kids will decide things for themselves.

184
00:13:17,560 --> 00:13:18,720
Goodbye.

185
00:13:30,320 --> 00:13:33,400
Times really have changed, haven't they?

186
00:13:33,480 --> 00:13:36,600
So from now on,
I suppose I can't interfere

187
00:13:36,680 --> 00:13:38,320
with Rat anymore, can I?

188
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:41,280
With the utmost respect, ma'am,

189
00:13:41,880 --> 00:13:44,560
let me say this sincerely,

190
00:13:44,640 --> 00:13:47,720
Ms. Kluay
is very well suited to Mr. Warat.

191
00:13:47,800 --> 00:13:49,800
If they really love each other,

192
00:13:49,880 --> 00:13:52,920
then we should let them
get to know each other on their own.

193
00:14:01,400 --> 00:14:04,160
Was I right or wrong

194
00:14:04,240 --> 00:14:06,480
not to stop Rat from the beginning?

195
00:14:09,480 --> 00:14:15,000
Rat being Vanich's heir
is already dangerous enough.

196
00:14:15,680 --> 00:14:18,320
I'm sorry, ma'am.

197
00:14:18,400 --> 00:14:22,240
When it comes to love,
you really can't force the heart.

198
00:14:33,280 --> 00:14:35,680
But people still have duties.

199
00:14:35,760 --> 00:14:38,040
Especially Rat himself.

200
00:14:38,120 --> 00:14:40,120
He should know in his own heart

201
00:14:40,200 --> 00:14:42,280
who is worthy of him.

202
00:14:42,360 --> 00:14:45,160
With the utmost respect, ma'am,

203
00:14:46,720 --> 00:14:49,520
the last time I saw Mr. Wichan smile

204
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:51,720
was when…

205
00:14:58,840 --> 00:15:01,040
Here. Oh, careful, dear.

206
00:15:01,640 --> 00:15:02,880
His neck is still weak. Support his neck.

207
00:15:03,400 --> 00:15:04,720
Oh, be careful.

208
00:15:05,720 --> 00:15:07,120
Supol, what is it?

209
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:10,240
The car is ready now, Mr. Wichan.

210
00:15:12,840 --> 00:15:16,280
Today our brave little one
has to go get vaccinated.

211
00:15:17,720 --> 00:15:18,800
Dear,

212
00:15:19,640 --> 00:15:21,880
do you think it will hurt her?

213
00:15:22,520 --> 00:15:23,920
She won't remember it.

214
00:15:25,680 --> 00:15:27,040
But I'm afraid it will hurt her.

215
00:15:28,400 --> 00:15:29,280
Can I be the one who gets hurt instead?

216
00:15:29,360 --> 00:15:31,440
Who can take that kind of pain
for someone else?

217
00:15:32,640 --> 00:15:34,280
Let's go.

218
00:15:35,560 --> 00:15:36,600
Dear.

219
00:15:37,960 --> 00:15:38,960
Yes?

220
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:43,000
Let's stay together like this forever.

221
00:15:47,200 --> 00:15:48,120
Yes.

222
00:15:56,440 --> 00:15:58,880
I really feel sorry for Mr. Wichan, ma'am.

223
00:16:01,520 --> 00:16:03,360
I must have done wrong, then.

224
00:16:03,960 --> 00:16:05,600
You did your best.

225
00:16:06,400 --> 00:16:07,880
You truly did it for everyone.

226
00:16:13,440 --> 00:16:15,200
Let's go. Drive.

227
00:16:15,720 --> 00:16:17,000
Yes, ma'am.

228
00:16:20,040 --> 00:16:20,880
Go.

229
00:16:38,640 --> 00:16:42,960
May the merit from today
be dedicated to Wichan,

230
00:16:43,040 --> 00:16:46,360
Ampha, and Praewilai.

231
00:16:46,440 --> 00:16:50,080
And may all the merit from today

232
00:16:50,160 --> 00:16:54,840
lead me to finding Waree

233
00:16:54,920 --> 00:16:57,160
very soon.

234
00:16:57,240 --> 00:16:58,640
Sathu.

235
00:17:00,120 --> 00:17:02,480
Is something troubling you?

236
00:17:03,080 --> 00:17:03,960
Yes, venerable sir.

237
00:17:04,040 --> 00:17:08,720
And is that matter
something you yourself did?

238
00:17:09,319 --> 00:17:10,760
I didn't do it.

239
00:17:10,839 --> 00:17:14,000
Then who did it?

240
00:17:24,359 --> 00:17:26,079
The restroom is so far away.

241
00:18:21,960 --> 00:18:22,920
What are you doing here?

242
00:18:23,560 --> 00:18:25,360
I saw you leave for the restroom

243
00:18:26,520 --> 00:18:27,640
and not come back for a long time.

244
00:18:28,280 --> 00:18:30,520
I've only been here for a moment.

245
00:18:32,160 --> 00:18:33,320
I missed you.

246
00:18:34,680 --> 00:18:37,400
- So cheesy. We're at work.
- Let's go, let's go.

247
00:18:38,360 --> 00:18:39,320
Go where?

248
00:18:39,400 --> 00:18:40,960
- Come on.
- Hey.

249
00:18:41,040 --> 00:18:43,240
But I felt like there was something

250
00:18:43,320 --> 00:18:45,240
- behind me.
- Hey, you're imagining it.

251
00:18:45,320 --> 00:18:47,800
And what if I'm not imagining it?

252
00:18:47,880 --> 00:18:49,160
You are imagining it.

253
00:18:53,040 --> 00:18:53,880
Arnon.

254
00:19:19,480 --> 00:19:20,680
What is it?

255
00:19:21,560 --> 00:19:23,040
Where's Mr. Arnon?

256
00:19:23,120 --> 00:19:24,360
He usually leaves with you.

257
00:19:24,440 --> 00:19:26,840
Maybe he went to
take care of some errand nearby.

258
00:19:27,400 --> 00:19:29,680
What kind of errand at a time like this?

259
00:19:30,440 --> 00:19:33,800
I don't know.
Maybe he went to buy a ring for Som.

260
00:19:34,440 --> 00:19:36,440
Huh? Really?

261
00:19:43,320 --> 00:19:45,760
No… nothing, Auntie.

262
00:19:47,840 --> 00:19:49,560
I'm not lying.

263
00:19:50,880 --> 00:19:52,920
It's the storage room.

264
00:19:54,480 --> 00:19:56,640
The weather's been cold lately,

265
00:19:56,720 --> 00:19:58,400
so snakes got in there and hid.

266
00:20:45,600 --> 00:20:47,160
Sin, don't!

267
00:20:52,240 --> 00:20:53,440
Why are you here?

268
00:20:54,040 --> 00:20:57,000
Doesn't matter. Don't open that door.

269
00:20:57,080 --> 00:20:59,240
Come on. We already
took Aunt Nong somewhere else

270
00:20:59,320 --> 00:21:01,120
so we could finally find out
what's in here.

271
00:21:04,560 --> 00:21:07,160
I just had a dream.

272
00:21:12,400 --> 00:21:15,200
And you're going to believe that?
Are you just talking nonsense?

273
00:21:22,680 --> 00:21:24,160
Sin, turn around and look behind you.

274
00:21:28,200 --> 00:21:30,600
- Then I'm opening it now.
- Hey, Sin!

275
00:21:32,800 --> 00:21:35,200
Calm down. Don't open it yet.

276
00:21:36,120 --> 00:21:39,560
I don't want to know anymore

277
00:21:39,640 --> 00:21:41,360
what's inside your aunt's room.
I don't want to know.

278
00:21:41,440 --> 00:21:43,600
- Don't open it.
- Why? Why don't you want to know?

279
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:48,360
Come on. As the owner of this house,
I'm ordering you.

280
00:21:48,440 --> 00:21:50,360
Do not open that door. Understand?

281
00:21:50,440 --> 00:21:51,480
You're really saying it like that?

282
00:21:52,080 --> 00:21:53,040
Sin,

283
00:21:53,960 --> 00:21:56,400
if you won't listen to me
as the owner of this house,

284
00:21:57,040 --> 00:21:58,440
then I'm begging you.

285
00:21:58,520 --> 00:22:01,280
Please don't open that door.
I'm begging you.

286
00:22:01,360 --> 00:22:02,200
Please.

287
00:22:05,120 --> 00:22:06,480
Alright. I won't open it.

288
00:22:11,640 --> 00:22:13,200
What is wrong with you?

289
00:22:36,880 --> 00:22:38,240
Keep watch on her.

290
00:22:53,240 --> 00:22:55,680
<i>We've caught her now.</i>
<i>We'll force everything out of her.</i>

291
00:23:21,440 --> 00:23:22,680
Where do you think Arnon went?

292
00:23:29,600 --> 00:23:32,360
Hey, untie me. Hurry up.

293
00:23:32,440 --> 00:23:33,440
Hurry.

294
00:23:40,040 --> 00:23:42,160
Anong, I got away already.

295
00:23:43,040 --> 00:23:44,000
I gotta go now.

296
00:23:49,320 --> 00:23:50,320
Where is she?

297
00:24:02,240 --> 00:24:03,680
Are you going to explain now?

298
00:24:05,320 --> 00:24:06,360
Explain what?

299
00:24:09,520 --> 00:24:11,960
Your dad's quite charming.

300
00:24:14,760 --> 00:24:17,720
At the time I was
talking to you on the phone,

301
00:24:17,800 --> 00:24:19,240
I really was with my father.

302
00:24:19,800 --> 00:24:23,440
And there was still a long time
before we met at the mall.

303
00:24:24,600 --> 00:24:25,760
You're lying.

304
00:24:27,640 --> 00:24:28,880
I'm not lying.

305
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:32,480
You are. And you know it in your heart.

306
00:24:35,920 --> 00:24:36,920
Think whatever you want.

307
00:24:38,200 --> 00:24:39,680
Uh, Det.

308
00:24:41,800 --> 00:24:43,400
What do you mean,
"Think whatever you want"?

309
00:24:44,080 --> 00:24:46,760
- Just whatever you want.
- Will you stop playing these crazy games?

310
00:24:46,840 --> 00:24:49,520
What game? I just went to work.

311
00:24:49,600 --> 00:24:51,840
That four-way love affair game of yours.

312
00:24:52,440 --> 00:24:54,520
Why do you enjoy making
people's relationships fall apart?

313
00:24:55,120 --> 00:24:56,680
I'm not playing games.

314
00:24:56,760 --> 00:25:00,200
And this matter
doesn't even concern anyone.

315
00:25:01,640 --> 00:25:06,000
Go ahead then. if you want
our relationship to get worse, go ahead.

316
00:25:06,080 --> 00:25:08,640
You're the one
making our relationship worse.

317
00:25:08,720 --> 00:25:11,280
What did I do? I just went to work.

318
00:25:11,360 --> 00:25:13,200
Talking business,
do you know what that is?

319
00:25:14,520 --> 00:25:16,760
What kind of business
requires lying down together to talk?

320
00:25:19,560 --> 00:25:23,360
You're just a servant's child.
Don't you dare get mouthy with me.

321
00:25:45,160 --> 00:25:47,000
- Don't get out yet.
- What is it?

322
00:25:47,080 --> 00:25:48,800
Why are you acting so strange?

323
00:25:48,880 --> 00:25:51,040
Because we just got engaged.

324
00:25:53,000 --> 00:25:56,600
The moment you open your mouth,
I already know you're lying. What is it?

325
00:25:59,080 --> 00:26:00,480
What? What?

326
00:26:02,240 --> 00:26:03,440
What?

327
00:26:14,000 --> 00:26:15,520
So what's wrong?

328
00:26:16,160 --> 00:26:18,160
- I'm worried about you, Kluay.
- About what?

329
00:26:19,400 --> 00:26:22,600
About what happened to you,

330
00:26:24,000 --> 00:26:26,880
how you were poisoned, and…

331
00:26:27,880 --> 00:26:31,600
how the thief broke into Baan Saeng.

332
00:26:31,680 --> 00:26:35,440
I think the thief
who broke into Baan Saeng

333
00:26:35,520 --> 00:26:37,880
might just have come for the documents.

334
00:26:38,440 --> 00:26:42,120
And the poisoning,

335
00:26:42,880 --> 00:26:44,960
it might just have been food poisoning.

336
00:26:47,320 --> 00:26:48,160
I'm sorry, Kluay.

337
00:26:48,760 --> 00:26:49,880
What are you sorry for?

338
00:26:49,960 --> 00:26:51,960
Arnon and I think

339
00:26:53,160 --> 00:26:54,840
that their real target is you.

340
00:26:56,280 --> 00:26:57,120
Me?

341
00:26:57,200 --> 00:27:00,280
Yes. Do you remember that woman?

342
00:27:00,880 --> 00:27:01,800
Near the restroom?

343
00:27:04,200 --> 00:27:06,080
I'm not sure.

344
00:27:07,560 --> 00:27:10,840
That woman wasn't one of our staff, Kluay.

345
00:27:11,600 --> 00:27:15,320
What? If she wasn't one of ours,
then how did she get into our company?

346
00:27:15,400 --> 00:27:17,720
Mr. Arnon found her

347
00:27:19,080 --> 00:27:20,400
on the CCTV footage.

348
00:27:22,880 --> 00:27:24,360
This feels really strange.

349
00:27:24,440 --> 00:27:27,480
Good thing Mr. Arnon got there in time.

350
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:32,440
That's why the two of us think
what happened to you

351
00:27:33,200 --> 00:27:34,760
may not have been a coincidence.

352
00:27:37,440 --> 00:27:39,440
They may know who you are.

353
00:27:40,080 --> 00:27:43,360
But if we find out first,
we'll have the advantage.

354
00:27:44,200 --> 00:27:47,840
And how are we supposed to find out?
Mama Toi has never told me anything.

355
00:27:48,440 --> 00:27:51,880
The only way we'll know
is to force it out of them.

356
00:27:53,160 --> 00:27:55,120
Because Arnon already caught her.

357
00:28:01,680 --> 00:28:02,920
Hello, Mr. Arnon.

358
00:28:07,800 --> 00:28:09,120
They escaped?

359
00:28:10,800 --> 00:28:12,360
Then what were you doing?

360
00:28:18,880 --> 00:28:19,760
They got away.

361
00:28:22,680 --> 00:28:24,000
What do we do now?

362
00:28:27,880 --> 00:28:28,880
I think…

363
00:28:38,560 --> 00:28:40,480
Everything is ready now, ma'am.

364
00:28:41,000 --> 00:28:44,280
Supol,
I made the right decision, didn't I?

365
00:28:45,840 --> 00:28:47,560
You did, ma'am.

366
00:28:48,240 --> 00:28:51,280
Mr. Warat is grown up enough now
to become the chairman of Vanich.

367
00:28:51,360 --> 00:28:55,560
And with your support,
I'm certain everything will go well.

368
00:28:56,120 --> 00:28:59,920
Most importantly,
you'll finally have time to rest too.

369
00:29:00,840 --> 00:29:02,720
Is everyone here yet?

370
00:29:03,320 --> 00:29:04,680
Yes, everyone is here, ma'am.

371
00:29:11,640 --> 00:29:13,200
How did they manage to escape?

372
00:29:15,000 --> 00:29:16,440
Because we've got a mole.

373
00:29:17,840 --> 00:29:19,600
- A mole?
- Yes.

374
00:29:20,160 --> 00:29:23,600
He's been with us for a long time.
They must have bought him off.

375
00:29:26,440 --> 00:29:28,160
Then who can we trust now?

376
00:29:28,680 --> 00:29:31,320
They have both money and power.

377
00:29:32,560 --> 00:29:34,240
We can't trust anyone anymore.

378
00:29:35,000 --> 00:29:37,000
What do you think they really want?

379
00:29:37,080 --> 00:29:38,600
As we already know,

380
00:29:39,560 --> 00:29:40,600
Ms. Kluay.

381
00:29:41,200 --> 00:29:43,480
I don't understand.
Why does it have to be Kluay?

382
00:29:43,560 --> 00:29:45,760
It must be connected to that will somehow.

383
00:29:45,840 --> 00:29:47,440
I still don't understand

384
00:29:48,440 --> 00:29:52,440
what benefit they get from hurting Kluay
and the will opening.

385
00:29:53,040 --> 00:29:54,120
I just can't figure it out.

386
00:29:54,200 --> 00:29:57,320
Ms. Anong is the one
most closely connected to all of this.

387
00:29:57,400 --> 00:29:58,920
But we don't have any evidence.

388
00:29:59,520 --> 00:30:00,960
I think you should accept the inheritance.

389
00:30:01,800 --> 00:30:03,280
Maybe things will get better.

390
00:30:05,240 --> 00:30:06,560
You know, right?

391
00:30:07,800 --> 00:30:09,480
That I don't want any of that stuff.

392
00:30:10,280 --> 00:30:12,760
I know. But accept it anyway.

393
00:30:15,160 --> 00:30:16,760
I don't want Grandma to be exhausted.

394
00:30:17,800 --> 00:30:18,880
I'm worried about her.

395
00:30:19,480 --> 00:30:22,440
Our company is full of ruthless people.

396
00:30:23,120 --> 00:30:24,680
But if…

397
00:30:26,240 --> 00:30:27,480
I'm not…

398
00:30:32,640 --> 00:30:33,520
Yes, Som?

399
00:30:45,800 --> 00:30:47,440
Everything is almost done, Auntie.

400
00:30:48,680 --> 00:30:50,160
Once everything is settled,

401
00:30:51,080 --> 00:30:52,680
I'll come and bring you back right away.

402
00:31:06,960 --> 00:31:08,200
Really?

403
00:31:10,720 --> 00:31:13,280
Yes. I saw it on the CCTV.

404
00:31:13,360 --> 00:31:15,680
- Last night, I also…
- What happened last night?

405
00:31:16,280 --> 00:31:19,240
- Last night, they broke into the office.
- Were they trying to hurt Kluay?

406
00:31:19,320 --> 00:31:22,280
They weren't trying to hurt her.
They were trying to kill her.

407
00:31:22,360 --> 00:31:23,640
They intended to kill her?

408
00:31:23,720 --> 00:31:25,520
I caught them,

409
00:31:25,600 --> 00:31:27,080
- but…
- But what?

410
00:31:27,680 --> 00:31:30,480
They got away.
I don't think this is ordinary anymore.

411
00:31:31,360 --> 00:31:34,400
You have to be very careful.
Because their target

412
00:31:34,480 --> 00:31:35,560
is Kluay.

413
00:31:35,640 --> 00:31:40,040
If their target is Kluay,
then should we find a bodyguard for her?

414
00:31:40,120 --> 00:31:43,600
Mr. Warat and I are already handling that.

415
00:31:43,680 --> 00:31:45,160
- But…
- But what?

416
00:31:45,240 --> 00:31:47,520
- I think there's a mole.
- What?

417
00:31:47,600 --> 00:31:48,920
<i>Even someone I thought</i>

418
00:31:49,000 --> 00:31:53,080
would never betray me
could still be bought off.

419
00:31:53,160 --> 00:31:54,760
Oh, Arnon.

420
00:31:55,320 --> 00:31:58,560
I'm not going to wait and let us
be the ones being attacked anymore.

421
00:31:58,640 --> 00:32:00,200
Then what are you going to do?

422
00:32:00,280 --> 00:32:02,480
If we bring Anong in
to talk and clear things up,

423
00:32:02,560 --> 00:32:04,200
then it will all be over.

424
00:33:04,080 --> 00:33:05,360
<i>Help me.</i>

425
00:33:05,440 --> 00:33:07,360
<i>H… Help…</i>

426
00:33:07,440 --> 00:33:09,000
<i>Please let me go.</i>

427
00:33:09,720 --> 00:33:11,640
<i>Help me. Help…</i>

428
00:33:15,600 --> 00:33:16,800
<i>Please let me go.</i>

429
00:33:18,280 --> 00:33:19,200
<i>Help me.</i>

430
00:33:19,800 --> 00:33:21,600
<i>H… Help…</i>

431
00:33:21,680 --> 00:33:22,720
Sin!

432
00:33:34,760 --> 00:33:37,280
- Uncle Rut!
- Sin!

433
00:33:38,000 --> 00:33:40,120
- Sin. Sin.
- Uncle. Uncle.

434
00:33:41,240 --> 00:33:43,200
- Sin.
- What's wrong, Uncle?

435
00:33:44,240 --> 00:33:45,080
Well…

436
00:33:45,160 --> 00:33:46,800
- I…
- What did you do?

437
00:33:46,880 --> 00:33:48,360
I grabbed the glass,

438
00:33:48,440 --> 00:33:50,560
but I may have grabbed it too hard,

439
00:33:51,080 --> 00:33:54,080
so it shattered in my hand.
Shattered in my hand.

440
00:33:54,160 --> 00:33:56,320
Forget it.
I think we should go get it treated.

441
00:33:59,360 --> 00:34:00,720
What happened to you?

442
00:34:02,400 --> 00:34:03,400
I think…

443
00:34:04,280 --> 00:34:05,240
I…

444
00:34:06,440 --> 00:34:07,800
Why is your body so hot?

445
00:34:10,560 --> 00:34:11,600
Mine? Hot?

446
00:34:13,239 --> 00:34:14,280
I think we should go.

447
00:34:14,360 --> 00:34:15,440
Go where?

448
00:34:17,199 --> 00:34:18,040
To the hospital.

449
00:34:18,639 --> 00:34:20,120
To the hospital. Huh?

450
00:34:20,199 --> 00:34:22,040
Hospital? Hey!

451
00:34:32,040 --> 00:34:36,360
Sin, actually, I can just rest at home.

452
00:34:36,440 --> 00:34:38,639
No. You have to go to the hospital.

453
00:34:38,719 --> 00:34:41,320
Aunt Nong isn't here.
What if something happens to you?

454
00:34:42,080 --> 00:34:43,639
And now you're about to go…

455
00:34:43,719 --> 00:34:45,760
Today is the day
Warat receives the inheritance.

456
00:34:51,840 --> 00:34:52,920
So, it's today.

457
00:35:26,400 --> 00:35:29,880
How did it go with the injection?
My good girl.

458
00:35:31,160 --> 00:35:33,000
I never thought

459
00:35:33,080 --> 00:35:35,200
you could be this adorable.

460
00:35:37,400 --> 00:35:38,560
Waree.

461
00:35:39,240 --> 00:35:41,040
I love you so much.

462
00:35:41,960 --> 00:35:46,320
Thank you for being born as my daughter.

463
00:35:50,760 --> 00:35:52,000
Do you know?

464
00:35:53,520 --> 00:35:55,520
All my life,

465
00:35:56,160 --> 00:35:58,040
I've suffered so much.

466
00:35:59,560 --> 00:36:01,000
Suffered so much that

467
00:36:02,760 --> 00:36:04,960
I didn't even know
when happiness would come.

468
00:36:06,680 --> 00:36:07,760
I suffered…

469
00:36:09,320 --> 00:36:10,760
so much that

470
00:36:12,240 --> 00:36:14,280
I didn't want to keep living anymore…

471
00:36:16,440 --> 00:36:20,280
if I had to wake up without knowing

472
00:36:20,880 --> 00:36:23,800
how life could ever be happy.

473
00:36:27,440 --> 00:36:30,160
But now, I don't care
about anyone else anymore.

474
00:36:31,600 --> 00:36:35,840
All I ask is to stay here with you,
to see you learn how to walk,

475
00:36:37,440 --> 00:36:39,080
to see you go to school,

476
00:36:40,600 --> 00:36:43,680
and to see your smile every single day.

477
00:36:45,960 --> 00:36:47,640
That alone makes me happy.

478
00:36:49,720 --> 00:36:51,400
Your smile

479
00:36:52,360 --> 00:36:53,560
makes me realize

480
00:36:55,240 --> 00:36:57,280
that all the suffering I endured,

481
00:36:57,920 --> 00:37:00,080
that staying alive until today,

482
00:37:00,800 --> 00:37:02,760
was all worth it.

483
00:37:07,360 --> 00:37:10,720
Thank you for being born as my daughter.

484
00:37:35,920 --> 00:37:37,960
Did Mr. Warat tell you anything?

485
00:37:39,240 --> 00:37:40,200
Could it be…

486
00:37:40,840 --> 00:37:43,520
Grandma,
can you tell me the truth just once?

487
00:37:43,600 --> 00:37:45,760
What exactly are you trying to say, Warat?

488
00:37:45,840 --> 00:37:48,760
NEXT EPISODE

489
00:37:49,920 --> 00:37:52,920
Det, you're going to be a father.

490
00:37:54,280 --> 00:37:57,320
- The child in your womb…
- Don't say it.

491
00:37:57,920 --> 00:37:59,200
It's not my child.

492
00:38:00,600 --> 00:38:02,160
Do as I told you.

493
00:38:07,760 --> 00:38:08,960
Mr. Warat?

494
00:38:09,960 --> 00:38:11,080
Let's break up.

495
00:38:11,880 --> 00:38:14,120
Why are you doing this to me?

496
00:40:38,720 --> 00:40:40,600
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
